  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\n\r\n/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**: Cloud providers are using the command-line tool `udevadm` to retrieve status and format volume mounts. `udevadm` is missing from the hyperkube image resulting in missing volumes.\r\n\r\nIssues: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/issues/43515 https://github.com/coreos/bugs/issues/2385\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nVolume mounts on cloud providers are expected to be formatted and mounted.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nGCE and Openstack volume mounts are effected.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.9, 1.10+\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: GCE and Openstack\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n",
